Wizards have crap AC, but honestly we aren't suppose to be tanking, buy my opinion is, if we are going to give out crap loads of dmg (which in Velious terms this means a whole 2% dmg to the mob before we are oom), we have no pets, enchanters, mages, necro's all get a pet line. Where as Wizard ait on our arse waiting for mana and getting hit everytime we sit down. Why not give us a AC bonus ? I love my iksar monk because of the AC bonus ( I mean come on, 860 ac at lvl 40, that rules ).<br>
<br>
As well, I would like to see a emergency type spell, a spell that could be used like DA for clerics, 10 sec invul. would be awesome. I hate camping orcs in HH for the stupid totem every other week just so it can maybe save my butt.<br>
<br>
As for others seeing our spell damages, Verant needs to get a friggin clue, why couldn't there be a option to see a casters damage like there is to see a melee's damage ? That makes no sense, honestly I think crit. nukes is a stupid idea (This is coming from a guy who got bored during lvl 52 and made a hotkey for ice comet that said, &quot;Techiex lands a critical nuke!(1120)&quot;, ask anyone on Bristlebane about that...).<br>
<br>
Also I would as well like to see a SoV DD spell for those 54 to 59, and it always makes me wonder, why don't Lure line spells increase in damage doing with lvl, like all of our other spells ? <br>
<br>
Why doesn't Verant increase the usefullness of Concussion ? My friend a few days ago told me it took 20 casts of concussion to work, which he thought was a bug of last week's patch.<br>
<br>
Question regarding Mages - WTF does verant think about mages, they must think mage is a god class. Why do I say this ? First off awesome pets, their pet is their strong point, now a lvl 57 mage can almost out-nuke a lvl 56 wiz ? WTF. Now mage's got CoH which made them more usefull, which I understand, but what's this BS of giving Mages DoT's, they already got a nice line of Rains, now verant gives them a DoT to play with. As well as the fact mages get spells that give them hp regeneration and mana regeneration, ok, what in the hell, they got their friggin pet out there, they rarely get beat on, why on earth do they have a shield that gives them hp and mana regen ? and why don't wizards have this spell ? I would kill for a hp regen spell, why ? because I actually have to take damage when I'm aggro'd, I wish I had a pet to sit there and taunt the mob for me.<br>
<br>
But after all this bs Verant has pulled on wizards, all I want is a lvl 55 pet spell, in which the pet is a baby dragon, that would friggin rule.<br>
<br>
-=[ techiex blu'draconis]=-<br>
-=[ 56 evoker of bristlebane ]=-<br>
